{\n  \"decision\": \"INCLUDE\",\n  \"reason\": \"The study measures intra-organizational boundary spanning behavior (External team communication) at the individual employee level (N=431) and provides a zero-order correlation matrix for these variables (Level 1).\",\n  \"quotes\": [\n    \"[Participants] Data was collected from 14 managers and 431 team members from 62 operational teams of a Chilean mining multinational.\",\n    \"[Measures] External team communication: We measured external team communication by asking how frequently team members communicated with members of other teams in the organisation. We utilised a three-item scale based on Ancona and Caldwell (1992).\",\n    \"[Appendix A] External Communication ... I share information with members from other teams within the organisation / I am in touch with people of the organisation external to my team / I engage in cross-functional activities\",\n    \"[Results] As the research is concerned with team-level phenomena, we collected data at both the level of the team-member (level 1) and the team (level 2). ... Table 1 shows correlations at the within- and between-person levels.\"\n  ],\n  \"matrix\": {\n    \"N\": 431,\n    \"correlations\": {\n      \"Team Education\": {\n        \"Team Education\": 1,\n        \"Team Tenure\": -0.26,\n        \"Standardisation\": 0.02,\n        \"P. Safety\": -0.01,\n        \"S. Innovation\": -0.07,\n        \"E.Communication\": 0.01\n      },\n      \"Team Tenure\": {\n        \"Team Education\": -0.26,\n        \"Team Tenure\": 1,\n        \"Standardisation\": -0.05,\n        \"P. Safety\": -0.02,\n        \"S. Innovation\": -0.04,\n        \"E.Communication\": 0.10\n      },\n      \"Standardisation\": {\n        \"Team Education\": 0.02,\n        \"Team Tenure\": -0.05,\n        \"Standardisation\": 1,\n        \"P. Safety\": 0.36,\n        \"S. Innovation\": 0.49,\n        \"E.Communication\": 0.38\n      },\n      \"P. Safety\": {\n        \"Team Education\": -0.01,\